 they got the support they needed.  One of my clients would say whenever she messed up by eating a ‚Äòbad‚Äô food like biscuits or chocolate she‚Äôd stop tracking her calories for the day and eat all the ‚Äòbad‚Äô food writing off the day!  She had black and white thinking about food which caused her to consistently overeat each time she ‚Äòmessed up‚Äô which was almost daily.  This made her feel bad physically from overeating as well as mentally by telling herself she was a failure. 
 
You don‚Äôt need to suffer on low calorie diets.  On paper, fat loss is easy.  In practise, for many, it‚Äôs a minefield.
 
Women will spend years stuck on the merry-go-round of losing weight on low calorie diets and regaining weight because they have chose an unsustainable approach, diets designed to illicit rapid (short lived) ‚Äòresults‚Äô.
 
You need to learn how to understand what your body is telling you (both physiologically and emotionally) and what it needs as a result.
 
Achieving a healthy level of body composition and maintaining your weight all year round is far more than simply eating fewer calories.
 
Biofeedback ‚Äì Your hunger, energy levels, appetite/ cravings, sleep quality, training performance and recover & your mood must be considered if we‚Äôre to build a diet that will stand the test of time.
 
Louise xx

